ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W3_LibraryBorrowingSystem

Class Name: LibraryBorrowingSystem

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 71 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a small library borrowing system that manages books, magazines, and members.
Use inheritance for shared item information, an interface for borrowable behavior,
ArrayList for storing objects, and exception handling for invalid actions.

Requirements
- Create LibraryItem as an abstract parent class.
- Create Book and Magazine as child classes.
- Make only Book implement Borrowable.
- Store items and members in ArrayList.
- Search by item ID and member ID.
- Borrow and return books.
- Use exception handling for invalid cases.

Learning Objective
Practice object-oriented design with inheritance, interface implementation,
collection-based search, state updates, and exception handling.
